Walk upstream on Primero Brazo from bridge 35m until 5m before large pool (looks good swimming). Up the bank to the right 2m on back side of 10cm dbh tree that leans away from the stream. Near ground.

On green stake in the middle of the breeding meadow where there‚Äôs a sandy shore. Device will probably get covered in mud quickly. At 10:37 I heard a single frog call ‚Äúmew‚Äù nearby and deployed a second recorder to record continuously for the time I‚Äôm here. There are two frogs within 30cm of device right now. More calls at 10:41-10:42 and more continuing until at least 11:30 intermittently. This is Waypoint 069 on gps
6 meters out on lodgepole pine with bark about 10 inches diameter directly across from campsite on point.
On limb on bottom of log (split log that goes onto shore) 6 meters from waters edge. SW side of lake w of outlet (ephemeral outlet).

Zip-tied to small rock and set in crack along bedrock outcrop on south side of lake (fairly well hidden; can't see from directly above because a small boulder blocks the view). Observed numerous adult RASI sitting at the bottom of this outcrop, including several individuals in amplexus. Only one small egg mass seen so far. Water temp 7.5 deg C. Rivendell_2_22June2024
Attached to submerged dead tree on east side of pond, about 8 feet out from shore. Several post-metamorphic RASI observed basking on tree. RivendellPond_1_22June2024

Emigrant14590_11June2024. Attached to small rock via zip tie and set on bottle close to base of willow on the north side of the large log submerged in the pond. Large RASI tadpoles from previous seasons present

Emigrant51106_11June2024. Attached to branch of only larger submerged log in the pond. Accessed from south side of pond. Completely snow and ice free, but no egg masses seen. Adjacent ponds to the south do have some snow fields still present. This was the pond in this cluster of ponds where I saw the most RASI tadpoles in 2023. Large RASI tadpoles from previous seasons were present. Also saw two T. elegans. Water temp at AudioMoth was 13.6 deg C.
ForniMeadow_Confluence_6June2024. Set just below confluence of two main channels at lower end of the upper meadow. Attached to part of submerged stump next to large boulders. Water temp 19.9 deg C.

ForniMeadow_Lower_6June2024. Attached to small willow branch near a small snowmelt inlet that is currently flowing. Jeff Mabe with ENF has seen adults and tadpoles here fairly consistently. Attached small piece of orange flagging on willow above the submerged attachment point. Water temp 15.7 deg C.

ForniMeadow_OldRoadXing_6June2024. Set on cutoff branch nub on submerged log at old road crossing. Orange flagging tied to cable above to mark spot. Lots of good egg mass attachment locations (no egg masses seen). Tadpoles often seen near here. Water temp 19.3 deg C.

ForniMeadow_Upper_6June2024. Set on downstream end of willow cluster by a small cascade next to a deep pool in the upper meadow. Two adults seen here and looks like a good spot for potential breeding. Water temp 18.9 deg C.
GooseLake1_Chellman_27May2024. Attached to underside of branch at usual egg mass hot spot. No egg masses observed yet! Water temp at recorder was 13.5 deg C.

GraniteLake_2260_1June2024. Set about a foot underwater on the underside of a large stick (~3.5 inch diameter), in among alders near southern inlet. Several RASI adults and at least 50 egg masses already present!

GraniteLake_2479_1June2024. Zip-tied to underside of submerged branch in the middle of a log jam at the mouth of the eastern outlet. Based on satellite imagery, Granite Lake melted out about 10 days ago, so deploying later than I wanted. Saw an adult female RASI right next to this spot (visible underwater in deployment picture). Tied a small piece of orange flagging to a log above water to aid in finding for retrieval. Water temp 15.1 deg C.‚Äô
HowardPond1_27May2024. Attached to submerged stump that has been an egg mass hot spot for the past several years. Water temp 2.7 deg C.

HowardPond2_27May2024. Zip tied to small willow stem right at edge of creek. Can‚Äôt see Audiomoth fron th surface, but it's tied to the base of the main stem, underwater. This was another egg mass hot spot in 2023. Water temp 2.7 deg C.
SWAMP001. On island looking thing, E side of lake, attached to rock.
SWAMP002. East Bank. ON inlet of S side of Island like feature. Attached to roots.
SWAMP003. On East Bank. Point half way up from the outlet. Attached to rock.
SWAMP004. East Bank. Second point south of the inlet. On the more north side of the point.
SWAMP005. East Bank. Last point south of the inlet (nearest the rock slabs). On the northern side of the point.
SWAMP006. North end of the lake 10-20 feet East of the the outlet. Within the log jam but on the outskirts. Attached to rock.

SWAMP007. West Bank.  On rock ramp that goes to one of the few water access on the west bank.  About halfway ish between the inlet and the outlet.  Picture is taken looking from the south towards the north (towards the outlet).  Small clump of trees on the bank here.  Attached to Rock

SWAMP008. West Bank.  Just south of the inlet on a small rock ramp that meets the water.  The picture is taken from the North looking South (I was essentially standing at the inlet when the pic was taken).  Attached to rock.
